Ethan M. Galindo Raya

Bio

Ethan Marcos Galindo Raya student of the Bachelor’s Degree in Genomic Sciences at National Autonomous University of Mexico (UNAM). Currently a research intern at FreyreLab, a laboratory mainly focused on bacterial regulation networks with a systems biology approach. He’d like to develop synthetic and computational biology in topics like morphogenesis, gene regulation networks and bioremediation.

Education

National Autonomous University of Mexico (UNAM) | Cuernavaca, Mexico

Undergraduate at Bachelor’s Degree in Genomic Sciences | August 2022 - Present

Experience

FreyreLab | Research intern | January 2023 - Present
